\begin_inset Formula $r,s\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 we define the 
\emph on
Schwartz norm
\emph default
:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\norm f_{r,s} & :=\sum_{\alpha,\abs{\alpha}\le r}\sum_{\beta,\abs{\beta}\le s}\sup_{x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}}\abs{x^{\alpha}\DD^{\beta}f\left(x\right)}
\end{align}

\end_inset

For example for 
\begin_inset Formula $r=0=s$
\end_inset

