\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
u\left(x\right) & :=\sup_{v\text{ subsolution}}\left(v\left(x\right)\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

For any domain this gives a harmonic function, but 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial\Omega$
\end_inset

 has to be sufficiently smooth, for the boundary condition to be satisfied.
